# Pem — Product Brief (Cursor)

See repo **`README.md`** (*What is Pem?*) for the human story. This file captures **technical product rules** for agents.

## Vocabulary

**Dump** (raw input) → **Prep** (unit of work — never “task”). **Prepping** / **Ready** / **Done** / **Archived** for status (`done` uses `done_at` like `archived` uses `archived_at`).

## Core loop

POST `/dumps` must **return immediately** after queuing BullMQ jobs — **never await** agents in the controller. One thought = one prep row = one job.

## Split vs intent (product direction)

- **Split** answers only: how many distinct thoughts / preps from one dump? (Unrelated asks → multiple preps; one coherent ask → one prep.) Implemented today in the dump worker (`SplitAgent`).
- **Intent routing** (see **`pem-intake-routing.mdc`**) is the target for **dynamic** handling per prep: classify each thought, then route (search vs draft vs clarify, etc.) so outputs match what the user needed — not one generic pattern for everything. DB `prep_type` / UI `PrepKind` may evolve to align with routed intents over time.

## Prep types

`search` | `research` | `options` | `draft` — map to UI `PrepKind` where needed.

## Status

`prepping` → `ready` ↔ `done` (toggle; `done_at` set when `done`). `archived` from active states. Failures stay `failed` (listed with prepping in hub). Restore from archived → `ready` (clears `done_at`).

## Schema

UUID PKs: `users`, `dumps`, `preps` — columns per brief (name, push_token, transcript, prep_type, status, summary, result jsonb, timestamps).

## Stack

NestJS + Vercel AI SDK (`ai` + `@ai-sdk/openai`), BullMQ + Redis, Drizzle + Postgres, Clerk, Tavily, OpenAI, Expo push.

## Rules

- No autonomous sends/purchases. **Pem never acts.**
- Options agent: **max 3 picks.**
- **maxSteps** capped for agentic tool use (see agents).

When in conflict with older code comments, **this brief wins** — update code to match.
